<div class="page-section__sub-section">
	<h4>Basic Tooltips</h4>
	<p>Basic tooltips are smaller and easier to markup. The content of the tooltip is passed into a component via the <code>data-tooltip</code> attribute. This attribute will <b>not</b> accept HTML. To direct the tooltip, the <code>data-direciton</code> attribute also needs to be set.</p>
	<div class="markup-panel">
		<div class="markup-panel__example">
<button role="button" class="ter-button ter-button--ghost" data-tooltip="This is a tooltip" data-direction="top">top tooltip</button>
<button role="button" class="ter-button ter-button--ghost" data-tooltip="This is a tooltip" data-direction="left">left tooltip</button>
<button role="button" class="ter-button ter-button--ghost" data-tooltip="This is a tooltip" data-direction="bottom">bottom tooltip</button>
<button role="button" class="ter-button ter-button--ghost" data-tooltip="This is a tooltip" data-direction="right">right tooltip</button>
		</div>
		<pre><code class="language-markup"></code></pre>
	</div>
</div>
<div class="page-section__sub-section">
	<h4>Advanced Tooltips</h4>
	<p>Advanced tooltips require more markup, but are more flexible, and <b>can</b> accept HTML tags, images, links, etc. Advanced tooltips wrap another component in a <code>.ter-tooltip</code> class. Just like the basic tooltips, advanced tooltips require the <code>data-direction</code> class to also be set.</p>
	<div class="markup-panel">
		<div class="markup-panel__example">
<span class="ter-tooltip" data-direction="top">
	<button role="button" class="ter-button ter-button--ghost">top tooltip</button>
	<span class="ter-tooltip__content">
		This is the same tooltip, but with <b>HTML tags</b> and <a href="#">links</a>
	</span>
</span>
<span class="ter-tooltip" data-direction="left">
	<button role="button" class="ter-button ter-button--ghost">left tooltip</button>
	<span class="ter-tooltip__content">
		This is the same tooltip, but with <b>HTML tags</b> and <a href="#">links</a>. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Suspendisse eu ultricies.
	</span>
</span>
<span class="ter-tooltip" data-direction="bottom">
	<button role="button" class="ter-button ter-button--ghost">bottom tooltip</button>
	<span class="ter-tooltip__content">
		This is the same tooltip, but with <b>HTML tags</b> and <a href="#">links</a>
	</span>
</span>
<span class="ter-tooltip" data-direction="right">
	<button role="button" class="ter-button ter-button--ghost">right tooltip</button>
	<span class="ter-tooltip__content">
		This is the same tooltip, but with <b>HTML tags</b> and <a href="#">links</a>
	</span>
</span>
		</div>
		<pre><code class="language-markup"></code></pre>
	</div>
</div>